### Default backend auth + member schema
### The backend currently exposes the schema route as /api/member/schema.

@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8080/api
@secretToken = not-really-a-key
@username = admin_hema
@password = supersecretpassword123
@email = admin@gmail.com

### 1. Ensure the default user exists
### This request is idempotent enough for local usage:
### 201 for created, 400 if the user already exists.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{secretToken}}

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "is_active": true,
  "member_id": null,
  "role_id": 1
}

### 2. Authenticate the default user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username={{username}}&password={{password}}

> {%
  client.global.set("auth_token", response.body.access_token);
%}

### 3. Call member schema
GET {{baseUrl}}/member/schema
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}
Accept: application/json
